=========================================
CALENDAR CLASS - METHODS & CONSTANTS NOTES
=========================================

Java Calendar Class – Reference Document

1. Introduction

Package: java.util

Type: Abstract class (extends Object, implements Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable<Calendar>)

Usage:
Calendar ek date–time abstraction hai jo year, month, day, hour, minute, second jaise fields ke saath kaam karta hai.
Locales aur time zones ke hisaab se adjust karne ke liye use hota hai.



---

2. Object Creation

Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance(); // Default locale & timezone
Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance(TimeZone tz);
Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance(Locale locale);


---

3. Important Fields / Constants

Months

JANUARY (0) → DECEMBER (11)
⚠️ Month 0-based hota hai.


Days of Week

SUNDAY (1) → SATURDAY (7)


AM/PM

AM (0), PM (1)


Other

HOUR, HOUR_OF_DAY, MINUTE, SECOND, MILLISECOND

DAY_OF_MONTH, DAY_OF_WEEK, DAY_OF_YEAR

WEEK_OF_MONTH, WEEK_OF_YEAR

ZONE_OFFSET, DST_OFFSET

1) add(int field, int amount): void
   - Kisi specific field (YEAR, MONTH, DATE, etc.) me amount add karta hai.
   - Overflow adjust hota hai (31 Jan + 1 month = 28/29 Feb).

2) after(Object when): boolean
   - Check karta hai ki current Calendar given object se baad me hai ya nahi.

3) before(Object when): boolean
   - Check karta hai ki current Calendar given object se pehle hai ya nahi.

4) clear(): void
   - Calendar ke saare fields reset kar deta hai (unset state).

5) clear(int field): void
   - Sirf ek specific field clear karta hai.

6) clone(): Object
   - Calendar ka ek deep copy banata hai.

7) compareTo(Calendar anotherCalendar): int
   - Current Calendar ko another se compare karta hai.
   - Return <0, 0, >0.

8) equals(Object obj): boolean
   - Compare karta hai ki do Calendar objects ka time & zone equal hai ya nahi.

9) get(int field): int
   - Given field (YEAR, MONTH, DAY_OF_MONTH, etc.) ka value return karta hai.

10) getActualMaximum(int field): int
    - Current context ke hisaab se max value deta hai (Feb → 28/29).

11) getActualMinimum(int field): int
    - Current context ke hisaab se min value deta hai.

12) getCalendarType(): String
    - Calendar ka type return karta hai (e.g. "gregory").

13) getClass(): Class
    - Runtime class ka object deta hai.

14) getDisplayName(int field, int style, Locale locale): String
    - Field ka readable naam return karta hai (e.g. MONDAY).

15) getDisplayNames(int field, int style, Locale locale): Map
    - Possible display names ka map return karta hai.

16) getFirstDayOfWeek(): int
    - Locale ke hisaab se week ka start day return karta hai.

17) getGreatestMinimum(int field): int
    - Sabse bada minimum jo kisi field ke liye valid hai.

18) getLeastMaximum(int field): int
    - Sabse chhota maximum jo kisi field ke liye valid hai.

19) getMaximum(int field): int
    - Field ke liye max value (general).

20) getMinimalDaysInFirstWeek(): int
    - Week 1 ke liye required minimum days.

21) getMinimum(int field): int
    - Field ke liye general minimum value.

22) getTime(): Date
    - Calendar ka current Date object return karta hai.

23) getTimeInMillis(): long
    - Epoch milliseconds (Jan 1, 1970 se) return karta hai.

24) getTimeZone(): TimeZone
    - Current Calendar ka timezone return karta hai.

25) getWeeksInWeekYear(): int
    - Current week-year me kitne weeks hain return karta hai.

26) getWeekYear(): int
    - ISO week-based year return karta hai.

27) hashCode(): int
    - Calendar ka hash code deta hai (equals ke saath consistent).

28) isLenient(): boolean
    - Calendar lenient hai ya strict.
    - Lenient true → invalid dates auto adjust.
    - Lenient false → error throw.

29) isSet(int field): boolean
    - Check karta hai ki field explicitly set hai ya nahi.

30) isWeekDateSupported(): boolean
    - Check karta hai ki week-date fields supported hain ya nahi.

31) notify(): void
    - Object method (thread notify) – rarely use.

32) notifyAll(): void
    - Object method (thread notify all).

33) roll(int field, boolean up): void
    - Field ko 1 step roll karta hai.
    - Overflow dusre fields ko affect nahi karta.

34) roll(int field, int amount): void
    - Field ko given amount roll karta hai without affecting others.

35) set(int field, int value): void
    - Specific field set karta hai.

36) set(int year, int month, int date): void
    - Year, Month, Date set karta hai.

37) set(int year, int month, int date, int hourOfDay, int minute): void
    - Year, Month, Date, Hour, Minute set karta hai.

38) set(int year, int month, int date, int hourOfDay, int minute, int second): void
    - Year, Month, Date, Hour, Minute, Second set karta hai.

39) setFirstDayOfWeek(int value): void
    - Week ka pehla din set karta hai (e.g. MONDAY).

40) setLenient(boolean lenient): void
    - Calendar ko lenient/strict banata hai.

41) setMinimalDaysInFirstWeek(int value): void
    - Week 1 ke liye minimum days set karta hai.

42) setTime(Date date): void
    - Calendar ka time ek Date se set karta hai.

43) setTimeInMillis(long millis): void
    - Epoch milliseconds se Calendar set karta hai.

44) setTimeZone(TimeZone value): void
    - Calendar ka timezone set karta hai.

45) setWeekDate(int weekYear, int weekOfYear, int dayOfWeek): void
    - Week-year format se Calendar set karta hai.

46) toInstant(): Instant
    - Calendar ka Instant representation return karta hai.

47) toString(): String
    - Calendar ka string representation deta hai.

48) wait(): void
    - Object method, thread wait.

49) wait(long time): void
    - Object method, timed wait.

50) wait(long time, int nanos): void
    - Object method, timed wait with nanos.

------------------------------------------------
CONSTANTS NOTES
------------------------------------------------
- ALL_STYLES: Style ke liye flag.
- AM, PM: Day half indicators.
- MONTHS: JANUARY (0) → DECEMBER (11), UNDECIMBER (12).
- DAYS: SUNDAY → SATURDAY.
- DATE, DAY_OF_MONTH, DAY_OF_YEAR, WEEK_OF_MONTH, WEEK_OF_YEAR:
  Different date tracking constants.
- ERA: BC/AD.
- HOUR, HOUR_OF_DAY, MINUTE, SECOND, MILLISECOND: Time units.
- ZONE_OFFSET, DST_OFFSET: Time zone adjustments.
- FIELD_COUNT: Total supported fields.
- Styles: SHORT, LONG, NARROW + FORMAT / STANDALONE variations.
- getAvailableCalendarTypes(): Supported calendar types ka set.
- getAvailableLocales(): All supported locales.
- getInstance(): Default Calendar instance.
- getInstance(Locale): Locale-specific Calendar.
- getInstance(TimeZone): Zone-specific Calendar.